<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Shutdown_or_Reboot_Stalled">Shutdown or Reboot Stalled</span></h3>
<p>There is a bug or known issue with the combination of SLiM, Xfce and systemd that does not let the system to properly shutdown and systemd waits for the SLiM service to end, but eventually is terminated. 
</p><p>To accelerate the shutdown process these lines might help when added to /usr/lib/systemd/system/slim.service:
</p>
<pre>[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/slim -nodaemon
Restart=on-failure
TimeoutStopSec=5s
IgnoreSIGPIPE=no
ExecStop=/bin/kill -TERM -${MAINPID}
</pre>
<p>See <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://bugs.archlinux.org/task/32380">FS#32380</a>.
</p>
